  "id": "phekb-liver-cancer-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "liver-cancer",
  "name": "Liver Cancer (HCC) - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query simulating a hepatology QI lead identifying ALL HCC patients across the system. Some patients have a coded HCC diagnosis; others were flagged via incidental elevated AFP without a formal diagnosis (Path D). The LLM should run two queries — by Condition and by elevated AFP Observation — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete liver cancer patient population for a hepatology quality initiative. Some patients have a formal hepatocellular carcinoma diagnosis on their problem list. Others have an incidentally elevated alpha-fetoprotein without yet having a formal diagnosis — these are often the highest-priority cases for follow-up imaging. Please run multiple FHIR queries to capture both groups: (1) patients with any liver cancer diagnosis on their problem list, and (2) patients with AFP results at or above 100 ng/mL. Return the union of patients found.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all my liver cancer patients across the chart.",
    "broad": "Find all liver cancer patients — some have a coded HCC diagnosis, others may have only an elevated AFP without a formal diagnosis. Run separate queries for diagnoses and lab results, then return the union.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|187769009,http://snomed.info/sct|93870000,http://snomed.info/sct|94381002 — covers HCC diagnosis variants. (2) Observation?code=http://loinc.org|1834-1&value-quantity=ge100||ng/mL — captures elevated AFP without formal diagnosis. Union the patient IDs across both queries."
  },
